Selling without pedal and seat

Full ultegra 
Well kept, stiff but comfortable 
Fixed Price

The Scenero of two years ago was a sublime ride, but if something can be more sublime ‚Äì sublimer perhaps ‚Äì then this is it. The Scenero‚Äôs balance of stiffness in the right places means that any increase in cadence is instantly rewarded with hyper-speed acceleration momentum. Every watt of your power seems to be directly delivered to the rear wheel, pushing you forward, fast.

Power is, of course, nothing without control, and the G2 handles with a dizzying blend of sharpness and precision ‚Äì a minimum twitch of your body and the lightest touch on the bar results in a point-and-shoot response that makes you feel like a hero even if you‚Äôre just turning into your drive. 

Credit here to the awesome Stiletto fork ‚Äì it‚Äôs laterally stiff but it kills vibration and chatter from the road. The Scenero holds its line with absolute dedication and changes direction so fast from small inputs we reckon it‚Äôs the kind of bike a fighter pilot would nonchalantly lean up against his Typhoon.
